### **📖 Overview**

**Embedded AI** integrates **machine learning models directly into hardware**, enabling AI-driven decision-making **without relying on cloud computing**. These **low-power, high-efficiency AI systems** are the backbone of modern IoT devices, industrial automation, and real-time analytics.

**⚠️ Ethical Concern:** Embedded AI raises **new challenges in bias, security, and control**, particularly when used in **autonomous surveillance, military tech, and algorithmic policing**.

---

### **🚀 Why Embedded AI?**

✅ **Ultra-Low Latency** – AI inference happens **on-device**, eliminating the delay of cloud processing.  
✅ **Energy Efficiency** – Optimized for **low-power devices**, reducing computational overhead.  
✅ **Privacy & Security** – Data is processed locally, **reducing exposure to third-party tracking**.  
✅ **Resilient AI** – Operates even **without an internet connection**, crucial for remote or mission-critical applications.

⚠️ **Ethical Risk:** AI models **baked into hardware** may be **hard to audit, modify, or remove** if they cause harm.

---

### **🔌 Key Applications of Embedded AI**

✅ **Wearable Technology** – Smartwatches, fitness trackers, and **biometric authentication**.  
✅ **Autonomous Vehicles** – AI-driven **navigation, object detection, and driver assistance**.  
✅ **Smart Home Devices** – AI-powered **voice assistants, energy management, and security systems**.  
✅ **Medical & Assistive AI** – AI-driven **hearing aids, prosthetics, and diagnostics tools**.  
✅ **Industrial IoT (IIoT)** – AI-enhanced **predictive maintenance, automation, and defect detection**.

⚠️ **Ethical Risk:** AI-powered **biometric surveillance in public spaces** raises **privacy & civil rights concerns**.

**Related Notes:** [[algorithmic-policing]] | [[automation-ethics]] | [[ai-ml-bias-mitigation]]

